Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool overcharge:1 Overcharge flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool sleepThresh:1 Sleep threshold flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool tempChThresh:1 Temperature threshold for storage element charging flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool tempDisThresh:1 Temeperature threshold for storage element discharging flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

uint8_t __reserved:1 reserved
bool src1MPPTStart:1 SRC1 MPPT start flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool src1MPPTDone:1 SRC1 MPPT done flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool src2MPPTStart:1 SRC2 MPPT start flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool src2MPPTDone:1 SRC2 MPPT done flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool storageDone:1 STO ADC done flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool tempDone:1 Temperature ADC done flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool APMDone:1 APM data ready flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

bool APMError:1 APM error flag.

Set to true if the flag is raised, to false otherwise

◆ AEM13920_IRQEN

struct AEM13920_IRQEN

IRQ settings.

Data Fields
bool enableOutOfReset:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the AEM is out of reset and ready to communicate.

Set to true to enable, to false to disable

bool enableDischarge:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the storage level is under the discharge threshold defined in AEM13920_Config::dischargeThresh.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableChargeReady:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the storage level is above the charge ready threshold defined in AEM13920_Config::chargeReadyThresh.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableOvercharge:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the storage level is above the overcharge threshold defined in AEM13920_Config::overchargeThresh.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableSleepThresh:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the source voltage drops below the defined threshold.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableTempChThresh:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the ambient temperature is out of the defined range for storage element charging.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableTempDisThresh:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the ambient temperature is out of the defined range for storage element discharging.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

uint8_t __reserved:1 reserved
bool enableSrc1MPPTStart:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on MPPT start for SRC1.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableSrc1MPPTDone:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on MPPT done for SRC1.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableSrc2MPPTStart:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on MPPT start for SRC2.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableSrc2MPPTDone:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on MPPT done for SRC2.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableStorageDone:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on STO ADC done.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableTempDone:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on temperature ADC done.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableAPMDone:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts when the APM data is ready.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

bool enableAPMError:1 Enable/Disable the generation of interrupts on APM errors.

Set to 1 to enable, to false to disable

◆ AEM13920_Status

struct AEM13920_Status

Status.

Data Fields
bool discharge:1 Discharge status.

Set to true when the storage level is under the discharge threshold defined in AEM13920_Config::dischargeThresh, to false otherwise

bool chargeReady:1 Charge ready status.

Set to true when the storage level is above the charge ready threshold defined in AEM13920_Config::chargeReadyThresh, to false otherwise

bool overcharge:1 Overcharge status.

Set to true when the storage level is above the overcharge threshold defined in AEM13920_Config::overchargeThresh, to false otherwise

bool src1Sleep:1 Sleep threshold on SRC1 status.

Set to true when the source voltage is under the defined sleep threshold, to false otherwise

bool src2Sleep:1 Sleep threshold on SRC2 status.

Set to true when the source voltage is under the defined sleep threshold, to false otherwise

uint8_t __reserved0:3 reserved
bool tempColdCharge:1 Cold temperature threshold for storage element charging status.

Set to true when the temperature is out of the defined range, to false otherwise

bool tempHotCharge:1 Hot temperature threshold for storage element charging status.

Set to true when the temperature is out of the defined range, to false otherwise

bool tempColdDischarge:1 Cold Temperature threshold for storage element discharging status.

Set to true when the temperature is out of the defined range, to false otherwise

bool tempHotDischarge:1 Hot temperature threshold for storage element discharging status.

Set to true when the temperature is out of the defined range, to false otherwise

uint8_t __reserved1:4 reserved

◆ AEM13920_APMERR

struct AEM13920_APMERR

APM Error.

Data Fields
bool src1CountOverflow:1 SRC1 counter overflow.

Set to true when a counter overflow has occured, to false otherwise

bool src1CountCorrupted:1 SRC1 counter corrupted.

Set to true when the counter is corrupted, to false otherwise

bool src2CountOverflow:1 SRC2 counter overflow.

Set to true when a counter overflow has occured, to false otherwise

bool src2CountCorrupted:1 SRC2 counter corrupted.

Set to true when the counter is corrupted, to false otherwise

bool buckCountOverflow:1 BUCK counter overflow.

Set to true when a counter overflow has occured, to false otherwise

bool buckCountCorrupted:1 Buck counter corrupted.

Set to true when the counter is corrupted, to false otherwise

uint8_t __reserved:2 reserved
